input:
Bob is big. Dave is blue. Dave is nice. Dave is round. Erin is nice. Erin is smart. Fiona is big. Fiona is blue. Fiona is not nice. Fiona is round. If Bob is red then Bob is not big. If Erin is round then Erin is big. Round, blue people are big. If Erin is red then Erin is white. If someone is nice and white then they are round. All red, white people are round. If Erin is red then Erin is nice. If someone is red and big then they are blue. If someone is smart then they are red. Question: Erin is not blue.?

universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Bob : obj
constant Dave : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Fiona : obj

constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Smart : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Big Bob
axiom T2 : Blue Dave
axiom T3 : Nice Dave
axiom T4 : Round Dave
axiom T5 : Nice Erin
axiom T6 : Smart Erin
axiom T7 : Big Fiona
axiom T8 : Blue Fiona
axiom T9 : ¬ Nice Fiona
axiom T10 : Round Fiona

axiom R1 : Red Bob → ¬ Big Bob
axiom R2 : Round Erin → Big Erin
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Round x ∧ Blue x → Big x
axiom R4 : Red Erin → White Erin
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ White x → Round x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ White x → Round x
axiom R7 : Red Erin → Nice Erin
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ Big x → Blue x
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Smart x → Red x

theorem erin_is_not_blue : ¬ Blue Erin :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem erin_is_not_blue : ¬ Blue Erin :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Red Erin := R9 Erin T6,
  have H2 : Blue Erin := R8 Erin (And.intro H1 (R2 (R5 Erin (And.intro T5 (R4 H1))))),
  contradiction,
end

-- The answer is True
